  "prompt": "What are the jersey numbers of famous soccer players?",
  "response": "Jersey numbers are iconic in soccer, often associated with specific players who have made significant impacts on the sport. Here's a list of some famous soccer players and the jersey numbers they are best known for:\n\n### Number 1\n- **Gianluigi Buffon**: Legendary Italian goalkeeper known for his time with Juventus and the Italian national team.\n- **Manuel Neuer**: Prominent German goalkeeper playing for Bayern Munich.\n\n### Number 7\n- **Cristiano Ronaldo**: Portuguese superstar currently wearing number 7 for Al Nassr and the Portugal national team. It's one of the most famous numbers in modern football.\n- **David Beckham**: English icon who famously wore number 7 for Manchester United, Real Madrid, and the England national team.\n- **Kylian Mbapp\u00e9**: French forward wearing number 7 for Paris Saint-Germain (PSG) and the France national team.\n\n### Number 9\n- **Robert Lewandowski**: Polish striker renowned for his goal-scoring prowess with Bayern Munich and the Polish national team.\n- **Karim Benzema**: French forward wearing number 9 for Real Madrid.\n- **Lionel Messi**: Although traditionally a number 10, Messi wore number 9 during his early days at FC Barcelona and has sported it occasionally.\n\n### Number 10\n- **Lionel Messi**: Argentine legend currently wearing number 10 for Inter Miami and the Argentina national team.\n- **Pel\u00e9**: Brazilian legend synonymous with the number 10.\n- **Diego Maradona**: Argentine great who famously donned number 10 during his career.\n- **Neymar Jr.**: Brazilian forward wearing number 10 for PSG and the Brazil national team.\n\n### Number 8\n- **Andr\u00e9s Iniesta**: Spanish midfielder known for his time at FC Barcelona, wearing number 8.\n- **Mo Salah**: Egyptian star wearing number 11 for Liverpool (historically noted for wearing number 11, but sometimes associated with midfield roles similar to number 8).\n\n### Number 6\n- **Sergio Ramos**: Spanish defender who wore number 4 at Real Madrid but has been associated with number 6 in other contexts.\n- **Paul Pogba**: French midfielder wearing number 6 for Juventus and the France national team.\n\n### Number 4\n- **Sergio Ramos**: Spanish defender famously wearing number 4 for Real Madrid and the Spain national team.\n- **Sergio Busquets**: Spanish midfielder wearing number 5 for FC Barcelona, but often linked with defensive midfield roles akin to number 4.\n\n### Number 11\n- **Neymar Jr.**: Brazilian forward wearing number 11 for PSG and has worn it for the Brazil national team.\n- **Ryan Giggs**: Welsh legend who wore number 11 for Manchester United.\n\n### Number 14\n- **Johan Cruyff**: Dutch maestro known for wearing number 14, which he made iconic.\n- **Thierry Henry**: French striker wore number 14 during his time at Arsenal.\n\n### Number 23\n- **David Beckham**: Later in his career, Beckham wore number 23 for LA Galaxy.\n- **Andr\u00e9s Iniesta**: Also has been associated with number 23 in certain team setups.\n\n### Other Notable Numbers\n- **Number 3**: Paolo Maldini (AC Milan), a symbol of defensive excellence.\n- **Number 5**: Zinedine Zidane (France national team), known for his elegant playmaking.\n- **Number 2**: Cafu (Brazil), renowned for his overlapping runs and defensive skills.\n\n### Current Stars and Their Numbers (as of 2023)\n- **Erling Haaland**: Valkyrie Wearing number 9 for Manchester City and the Norwegian national team.\n- **Kevin De Bruyne**: Belgian playmaker wearing number 17 for Manchester City, though traditionally associated with other numbers.\n- **Vin\u00edcius J\u00fanior**: Brazilian winger wearing number 20 for Real Madrid.\n\n*Please note that jersey numbers can change based on team transfers, player preferences, and club decisions. Additionally, some players may have worn multiple numbers throughout their careers.*",
